                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Pak frontier charge for IAF officer
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, April 2: Air Marshal Arup Raha has taken over as the senior air staff officer of the Western Air Command in New Delhi, overseeing operations in a theatre covering the Pakistan frontier and part of Chinas frontier in Ladakh.         
	A flight combat leader with about 3,400 hours of flying, Air Marshal Raha was air attach in Ukraine. He has been deputy commandant of the Air Force Academy and directing staff at the Flying Instructors School, Tambaram, and Tactics and Air Combat Development Establishment, Gwalior.        
	The air marshal has commanded the Black Archers MiG-29 squadron and two frontline bases in the Western Air Command. Before his current posting, he was commanding the Advance Head Quarters, Western Air Command, Chandimandir.        
	Also, Air Marshal Ajay Shriniwas Karnik has taken over as director-general (inspection and safety) at air headquarters.                                                                                                                                                           
